<br>
Well, all three of the characters I play have (or will have) places in XP groups.  Still, I do see where one group hogging a popular zone has the potential of being a problem.<br>
<br>
I would suspect that the answer to this dilemma would come from a compromise.  Some zone where Verant lodges it's collective head further up a local convenient orifice and falls back on old tactics, ie. "That spell cannot be used here".  Leave SOME zones open to PBAE groups and others closed would be my suggestion.  AE nukes have little place in a standard group with crowd control other than to clear greenies.  Perhaps nerf Chardok to no AE, and counterbalance with adding some MAGIC ONLY mobs that can't be harmed by weapons.  I think this game is WAY overdue for something like that anyway.  <br>
<br>
As an example, the terrain, spawns, and general layout of CS make it idea for the quad-kiterers, but it also makes it impossible for them to "camp" spawns because they're likely to be elsewhere on repop.  XP groups can also find work here.  Pulling the undersea chests at lower level, or the drakes and sirens at higher levels (hey - quadders LOVE dead drakes).  But the quadders can't kite in, for example, Chardok.  Quadwhiners with spell-envy and tiny penises aside, this is a good compromise.  Quadders in one place, xp-groupers usually somewhere else.  If quadkiters can have their place, then why can't PBAEs?  <br>
<br>
